com.symantec.dlpx.flexresponse.incident

Interface Incident


  • public interface Incident
    A Symantec DLP incident. An incident occurs when a policy is violated for a particular item of content.

      • getPreventOrProtectStatus

        PreventOrProtectStatus getPreventOrProtectStatus()
        Get the current prevent/protect status for the incident.
        Returns:
        The current prevent/protect status for the incident or null if the status value is unknown. Unknown values represent new status values defined in a newer version of the FlexResponse API passed to a plugin developed with an older version of the API.

      • getCustomAttribute

        CustomAttribute getCustomAttribute(java.lang.String attributeName)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Get a custom attribute. Custom attributes are defined by a Symantec DLP administrator for custom use within a given deployment.
        Parameters:
        attributeName - the name of a valid custom attribute defined in the system.
        Returns:
        the attribute with the given name. If the attribute currently does not have a value assigned for this incident, then the CustomAttribute.hasValue method will return false and the CustomAttribute.getValue() method will return null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if there is no attribute with this name defined in the system.

      • getCustomAttributes

        java.util.Collection<CustomAttribute> getCustomAttributes()
        Get all the custom attributes defined in the system.
        Returns:
        a collection of all available custom attributes. If a given attribute does not currently have a value assigned for this incident, then the CustomAttribute.hasValue method will return false and the CustomAttribute.getValue() method will return null.
